    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, my realtor just mentioned something about needing an escrow account for my house purchase here in Toronto. I've never dealt with this before, can you just explain what escrow actually is and why it's used during the closing process?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in the context of your house purchase in Toronto, is essentially a temporary holding place for funds and documents, managed by a neutral third party. Think of it like a secure, temporary holding cage for your money and the paperwork until all the conditions of the sale are met. It's crucial because it protects both you, the buyer, and the seller, ensuring that the money doesn't go to the seller until the buyer has received clear title to the property, and vice versa. The escrow agent makes sure the whole transaction proceeds smoothly, preventing any sudden, chaotic scrambles that might happen if you were just handing cash over directly to the seller.",
      "source": "target",
